1370
01:25:55,965 --> 01:25:58,593
Turn around, this is your favorite part.

1371
01:26:01,671 --> 01:26:04,196
She's wearing that hat you like.

1372
01:26:12,382 --> 01:26:16,079
That's my side, thank you very much.

1373
01:26:17,120 --> 01:26:19,020
Mother Teresa.

1374
01:26:23,760 --> 01:26:25,921
I love you too.

1375
01:26:43,213 --> 01:26:44,578
You like her?

1376
01:26:44,747 --> 01:26:46,647
- She's a handsome boat.
- Yeah.

1377
01:26:46,816 --> 01:26:49,216
Reminds one of the longboats
they would run...

1378
01:26:49,385 --> 01:26:51,945
...out of the sweet harbor at Bantry Bay.

1379
01:26:52,121 --> 01:26:56,455
Actually, I designed this one based
on a Portuguese boat.

1380
01:26:56,626 --> 01:26:58,423
But historically, you're correct, yeah.

1381
01:26:58,595 --> 01:27:00,790
- You built this boat yourself?
- Yes, sir.

1382
01:27:00,964 --> 01:27:02,693
- You build boats?
- No, no.

1383
01:27:02,865 --> 01:27:05,527
Truth be told, I don't know
the first thing about them.

1384
01:27:05,702 --> 01:27:08,728
- But I do appreciate a work of art.
- Well, thank you, sir.

1385
01:27:08,905 --> 01:27:12,841
I'm about to sell this work of art to a guy
who's gonna cut it in half...

1386
01:27:13,009 --> 01:27:14,840
...and stick it on his wall.
- Oh, no.

1387
01:27:15,011 --> 01:27:19,004
Yeah. I'm about to take her out for a last
paddle before I meet the butcher at noon.

1388
01:27:19,182 --> 01:27:20,877
Why would you do a thing like that?

1389
01:27:21,050 --> 01:27:24,451
It's a long story. Something about
the violation of expectations...

1390
01:27:24,621 --> 01:27:28,182
...and a crushing loss of faith
in love and life and art.

1391
01:27:28,358 --> 01:27:30,383
- So it's a girl.
- Yes.

1392
01:27:30,660 --> 01:27:33,458
I've had a little girl trouble
myself lately.

1393
01:27:33,630 --> 01:27:37,361
But better to have loved
and lost. Am I right?

1394
01:27:37,533 --> 01:27:40,161
She was a unique constellation
of attributes.

1395
01:27:40,336 --> 01:27:42,804
She was my Halley's comet.

1396
01:27:42,972 --> 01:27:45,532
But... Universe is designed
to break your heart, yes?

1397
01:27:45,708 --> 01:27:49,974
A philosopher as well as an artist.
Yes, it's we who suffer most.

1398
01:27:50,146 --> 01:27:53,843
Yes. With the possible exception
being the victims of violent crime.

1399
01:27:54,851 --> 01:27:59,220
- Well, it's been a pleasure to meet you, sir.
- No, no, pleasure's all mine. Jake.

1400
01:27:59,389 --> 01:28:02,017
- Bill. I have a daughter who would...
- No, no.

1401
01:28:02,191 --> 01:28:04,056
Never mind. No, no. Sorry.

1402
01:28:13,002 --> 01:28:15,232
Well, this is a surprise.

1403
01:28:15,405 --> 01:28:19,136
Can't a father pay a visit to his daughter
on a beautiful Sunday morning?

1404
01:28:19,309 --> 01:28:22,904
Carol called you, didn't she? She's afraid
I'm getting into my pajamas again.

1405
01:28:23,079 --> 01:28:26,742
Actually, carol called christine,
christine called Michael...

1406
01:28:26,916 --> 01:28:29,384
...Michael called me.
- Any word from Aunt Eileen?

1407
01:28:29,552 --> 01:28:32,612
She said to tell you that
casey Donovan was adopted.

1408
01:28:32,789 --> 01:28:34,347
If that helps.

1409
01:28:34,524 --> 01:28:37,459
Well, at this point, he's starting
to look awfully good.

1410
01:28:37,894 --> 01:28:39,919
He's out there, Sarah.

1411
01:28:41,197 --> 01:28:44,132
Someone who would appreciate
all you have to offer.

1412
01:28:46,002 --> 01:28:49,699
After all, you're this unique
constellation of attributes.

1413
01:28:49,872 --> 01:28:52,136
- You're Halley's comet...
- what did you just say?

1414
01:28:52,775 --> 01:28:55,175
It's a nice turn of phrase,
but it's not my own.

1415
01:28:55,345 --> 01:28:58,041
I heard it from a young man
I met this morning.

1416
01:28:58,214 --> 01:28:59,909
Builds beautiful Irish boats.

1417
01:29:00,516 --> 01:29:04,646
Poor lad. Had his heart broken
by a woman he deeply cared about.

1418
01:29:05,288 --> 01:29:06,778
Deeply.

1419
01:29:07,724 --> 01:29:11,216
- Jake. Jake!
- Hello there.

1420
01:29:11,394 --> 01:29:16,331
Hi. Hi, I'm looking for Jake.
Jake Anderson. Is he here?

1421
01:29:16,499 --> 01:29:19,798
- No, he isn't. But lucky for us, I am.
- I don't have time for this.

1422
01:29:19,969 --> 01:29:23,063
- Do you know where he is?
- You're "must love dogs," aren't you?

1423
01:29:23,239 --> 01:29:25,764
You've already crushed him,
he's been moping for weeks.

1424
01:29:25,942 --> 01:29:28,069
He's even given up
the whole wooden-boat thing.

1425
01:29:28,244 --> 01:29:30,109
- You've done enough.
- That's all wrong.

1426
01:29:30,279 --> 01:29:32,144
I have to talk to him. Where is he?

1427
01:29:32,348 --> 01:29:34,282
- I can't tell you that.
- Where is he?

1428
01:29:34,450 --> 01:29:36,247
I'm not telling you.

1429
01:29:37,653 --> 01:29:39,587
You know the bridge
by the boat ramp?

1430
01:29:48,264 --> 01:29:49,629
Jake?

1431
01:29:51,067 --> 01:29:52,625
Jake.

1432
01:29:53,403 --> 01:29:55,132
Jake!

1433
01:30:03,679 --> 01:30:07,240
- I'd like to rent a boat, please.
- I'm sorry, we're all out of boats.

1434
01:30:12,555 --> 01:30:15,490
- All right, come on.
- Oh, a love chase.

1435
01:30:15,658 --> 01:30:17,626
Come on, girl, you can do this.

1436
01:30:17,794 --> 01:30:21,230
This is really important to me.
Come on.

1437
01:30:21,697 --> 01:30:23,221
I think he could be the one.

1438
01:30:23,866 --> 01:30:25,333
Come on, girls, let's get going.

1439
01:30:25,701 --> 01:30:29,000
Push! Push!

1440
01:30:29,906 --> 01:30:33,069
Push! Push!

1441
01:30:33,242 --> 01:30:35,710
Push, push!

1442
01:30:35,878 --> 01:30:40,679
Push! Push! Push!

1443
01:30:40,983 --> 01:30:42,883
- Push!
- Push!

1444
01:30:43,052 --> 01:30:45,213
That's him. I see him!

1445
01:30:45,388 --> 01:30:48,357
Jake! Jake!

1446
01:30:51,727 --> 01:30:53,718
Stop the boat!

1447
01:30:54,063 --> 01:30:55,724
Never mind.

1448
01:30:59,669 --> 01:31:01,398
Okay, girl, here we go.

1449
01:31:01,571 --> 01:31:03,402
Jake!

1450
01:31:13,816 --> 01:31:15,841
Here she goes!

1451
01:31:20,356 --> 01:31:21,880
Jake.

1452
01:31:22,391 --> 01:31:24,188
What are you doing?

1453
01:31:25,394 --> 01:31:27,954
All right. Here we go.
All the way up. Almost.

1454
01:31:31,234 --> 01:31:32,531
- Come on, girl.
- Come on.

1455
01:31:32,702 --> 01:31:34,465
- Good girl, you can do it.
- Here we go.

1456
01:31:34,637 --> 01:31:36,662
- Watch your paws there.
- Easy, easy.

1457
01:31:41,878 --> 01:31:45,575
Cold. Cold. Very cold.

1458
01:31:47,984 --> 01:31:49,451
Here we go.

1459
01:31:51,754 --> 01:31:53,016
Thank you.

1460
01:31:54,757 --> 01:31:56,952
Was there something you wanted
to say to me?

1461
01:31:57,593 --> 01:31:59,117
Yes.

1462
01:31:59,295 --> 01:32:00,887
Could have just called.

1463
01:32:01,063 --> 01:32:03,896
Perhaps that would have been
the wiser course, yes.

1464
01:32:04,300 --> 01:32:05,892
What's up?

1465
01:32:07,069 --> 01:32:11,062
I owe you my story.
You asked me for honesty...

1466
01:32:11,240 --> 01:32:14,676
...and it scared the hell out of me,
and I held back...

1467
01:32:14,844 --> 01:32:17,404
...and I didn't want to let you
see the real me.

1468
01:32:17,580 --> 01:32:20,174
Because I was afraid
of getting hurt again.

1469
01:32:21,017 --> 01:32:25,420
But, listen, I hear that the universe
lets your heart expand...

1470
01:32:25,588 --> 01:32:29,217
...and grow back even bigger
after you go through all that pain.

1471
01:32:29,392 --> 01:32:32,793
Well, I believe that now.

1472
01:32:32,962 --> 01:32:35,988
And I was just wishing
there was a way that...

1473
01:32:36,198 --> 01:32:39,497
...I could have another chance
to make this work.

1474
01:32:49,579 --> 01:32:51,308
I'll be right with you.

1475
01:32:51,747 --> 01:32:53,977
Hi, how can l...?

1476
01:32:54,150 --> 01:32:55,447
Don't worry, I got it.

1477
01:32:55,618 --> 01:32:58,746
Single chicken breast, no dating advice,
coming right up.

1478
01:32:58,921 --> 01:33:01,822
Actually, I would like to have
three whole fryers, please.

1479
01:33:01,991 --> 01:33:05,017
And six pork chops and a lamb shank.

1480
01:33:05,194 --> 01:33:07,526
And do you have any dog bones
back there?

1481
01:33:09,031 --> 01:33:12,728
If you do, throw them in the cart.
What are the specials today?

1482
01:33:13,235 --> 01:33:14,361
Yes.

1483
01:33:25,715 --> 01:33:27,182
<i>Thank you.</i>

1484
01:33:31,821 --> 01:33:34,346
How many people
are actually in this family?

1485
01:33:37,393 --> 01:33:39,122
- Hey.
- Hey.

1486
01:33:39,295 --> 01:33:40,762
Get down.

1487
01:33:43,232 --> 01:33:44,529
Down!

1488
01:34:08,257 --> 01:34:09,918
How did we meet?

1489
01:34:10,092 --> 01:34:12,822
- Oh, that's a great story. Tell it, hon.
- Great story.

1490
01:34:12,995 --> 01:34:16,556
Well, actually,
it's a very romantic story.

1491
01:34:16,732 --> 01:34:18,791
- You tell it, carol.
- No, go ahead, honey.

1492
01:34:18,968 --> 01:34:22,199
No, no, really, you should.
She tells this story great.

1493
01:34:23,272 --> 01:34:25,001
You don't remember, do you?

1494
01:34:26,275 --> 01:34:29,301
Don't remember? How we met?

1495
01:34:35,851 --> 01:34:37,944
I don't remember.

1496
01:34:38,821 --> 01:34:40,914
But I love her.

1497
01:34:42,024 --> 01:34:43,252
I love her!

1498
01:34:43,426 --> 01:34:45,826
Love is not reserved for the young,
you know.

1499
01:34:46,162 --> 01:34:47,322
As the poet said:

1500
01:34:47,496 --> 01:34:50,158
<i>Grow old along with me!</i>
<i>The best is yet to be</i>

1501
01:34:50,332 --> 01:34:51,663
- Yeats?
- No.

1502
01:34:51,834 --> 01:34:54,029
- Tennyson?
- No.

1503
01:34:54,203 --> 01:34:56,433
- Browning.
- Browning.

1504
01:34:56,605 --> 01:34:58,368
Who knows her daddy?

1505
01:34:58,541 --> 01:35:02,568
Oh, my gosh, I did not think
I was ready to settle down...

1506
01:35:02,812 --> 01:35:05,406
...but look at the size of this rock.

1507
01:35:05,581 --> 01:35:09,347
And you want to know what else?
I'm gonna get a cute little tattoo...

1508
01:35:09,518 --> 01:35:12,078
...in someplace that's
N-o-N of your business.

1509
01:35:12,254 --> 01:35:15,451
And wanna know what it's gonna say?

1510
01:35:15,858 --> 01:35:18,759
"Mrs. Casey Donovan."

1511
01:35:21,030 --> 01:35:23,225
The best place to meet someone...

1512
01:35:23,399 --> 01:35:26,994
...is Parseghian's Armenian restaurant
in Koreatown.

1513
01:35:27,169 --> 01:35:29,501
I don't care if you're young,
you're old...

1514
01:35:29,672 --> 01:35:31,640
...you're single, you're divorced...

1515
01:35:32,975 --> 01:35:33,964
I'm getting there.

1516
01:35:35,411 --> 01:35:38,209
71 oo First Street.

1517
01:35:38,380 --> 01:35:41,178
Wednesday, mother-in-law night.

1518
01:35:41,350 --> 01:35:42,908
All she can eat.

1519
01:35:47,356 --> 01:35:49,722
- In a dog park.
- Dog park, yeah.

1520
01:35:50,059 --> 01:35:51,424
- It's true.
- I know.

1521
01:35:51,594 --> 01:35:53,118
I was very... I was nervous.

1522
01:35:53,295 --> 01:35:57,026
We had no idea at the time
that we could ever wind up...

1523
01:35:57,199 --> 01:35:58,723
oh, that's not true. I did.

1524
01:35:58,901 --> 01:36:00,425
- You did not.
- I did too.

1525
01:36:00,603 --> 01:36:03,163
- I have a theory about this.
- He has lots of theories.

1526
01:36:03,339 --> 01:36:05,739
I do. This is actually a good one.
I took some notes.

1527
01:36:05,908 --> 01:36:07,808
Oh, God, you're so prepared for this.

1528
01:36:08,010 --> 01:36:09,841
You grow up, you're an adult, right?

1529
01:36:10,012 --> 01:36:13,743
And you think you have all this worldly
experience, right? That's point A.

1530
01:36:13,916 --> 01:36:16,146
You think your personality is formed.

1531
01:36:16,385 --> 01:36:18,182
And then you think you're complete...

1532
01:36:18,354 --> 01:36:20,914
...but you meet somebody,
you start feeling new things.

1533
01:36:21,090 --> 01:36:23,490
And you start feeling
excruciatingly painful things.

1534
01:36:23,726 --> 01:36:27,355
You get confused, right?
You get nauseous.

1535
01:36:27,530 --> 01:36:31,762
And I think when you get really nauseous,
like that, it's, like, the completion of self.

1536
01:36:31,934 --> 01:36:34,630
The person who can fill the final void.

1537
01:36:34,837 --> 01:36:36,828
That's what it was like
when I met Sarah.

1538
01:36:37,006 --> 01:36:40,237
- I made you nauseous.
- In a good way. I was lovesick.

1539
01:36:41,844 --> 01:36:43,744
That was good, honey.

1540
01:37:54,083 --> 01:37:56,074
